reviews.review_text: New sound Pretty strong show. Great sound. Loving Vince
4/8/91 I think if Jerry's voice was as good as it was in Greensboro these shows would have gotten more attention. There is some killer Jerry guitar playing here !

Eyes of Jerry If you want anymore proof the Jerry was and forever an amazing guitarist, then listen to Eyes. He's just amazing with a jaw dropping fret work on his custom built. I had the total pleasure of being there for my second GD show ever. I am forever Grateful.

The Orlando Show 4/8/91 My first ever Dead show.  What a trip!  Two things that I remember most about that day.....The parking lot.  Remember how some vendors sold beer at $1 a Bottle/Can?  There was this one young guy that was doing so and had a cooler strapped to a skateboard. He stratled the cooler and rode along through the crowd selling beer singles until a cop stopped him right in front of me.  The cop hassled him for a minute or two and then yelled out that this guy was giving out free beer!  The crowd converged on this little guy and took all of his beer.  Once the cop walked away, everyone came back and gave him his beer back.  I was overwhelmed!  Then after the show as we were walking out of the arena yelling at the top of our lungs, we realized that there was tear gas in the air and we all started choking and coughing.  Anyone that was there remember that?  I guess there were some local punks that were throwing rocks and beer bottles at the dead-heads and rather than taking them awaym the cops just gassed everyone.
